        "articles"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 1773327277822,
      "title": "TRS / HEALTHSELECT",
      "content": "TRS / HealthSelect showing as OOS may still be processed.\n\nTRS and HealthSelect are fully insured only in the state of Texas.\n\nIf a claim has a TRS or HealthSelect policy number and the state is Oklahoma, it is considered OOS for NSA.&nbsp;<div>Reference: <a href=\"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:040d113871eb4d6bab8685db63548e85@thread.v2/1773843906989?context=%7B%22contextType%22%3A%22chat%22%7D\" target=\"_blank\">Link</a></div>",
      "createdAt": "Mar 12, 2026 09:54 AM",
      "createdBy": "Jasfer B.",
      "updatedAt": "3/26/2026, 4:00:57 PM",
      "updatedBy": "Jasfer B.",
      "visibility": [
        "articles"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 1773325130678,
      "title": "Ambetter and BAYLOR & SCOTT claims",
      "content": "EOB remark codes surpass the funding type.\n\nIt is very important to go by how the EOB was processed.\n\nException: Ambetter and Baylor &amp; Scott.&nbsp;<div>Reference: <a href=\"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:040d113871eb4d6bab8685db63548e85@thread.v2/1774280496477?context=%7B%22contextType%22%3A%22chat%22%7D\" target=\"_blank\">Link</a></div>",
